    Nelder-Mead Generator adapted from SciPy¶

    Most of the algorithms in scipy.optimize are self-contained functions that operate on the user-provided func. Xopt has adapted the Nelder-Mead directly from scipy.optimize to be in a generator form. This allows for the manual stepping through the algorithm.

    In [1]:
    Copied!

import numpy as np

    Nelder-Mead optimization of the Rosenbrock function with Xopt¶

    In [2]:
    Copied! 
    YAML = """
xopt: {}
generator:
  name: neldermead
  initial_point: {x0: -1, x1: -1}
  adaptive: true
  xatol: 0.0001
  fatol: 0.0001  
evaluator:
  function: xopt.resources.test_functions.rosenbrock.evaluate_rosenbrock
vocs:
  variables:
    x0: [-5, 5]
    x1: [-5, 5]
  objectives: {y: MINIMIZE}
"""
X = Xopt(YAML)
    YAML = """ xopt: {} generator: name: neldermead initial_point: {x0: -1, x1: -1} adaptive: true xatol: 0.0001 fatol: 0.0001 evaluator: function: xopt.resources.test_functions.rosenbrock.evaluate_rosenbrock vocs: variables: x0: [-5, 5] x1: [-5, 5] objectives: {y: MINIMIZE} """ X = Xopt(YAML)

    def plot_simplex(simplex, ax=None):
    x0 = simplex["x0"]
    x1 = simplex["x1"]
    x0 = np.append(x0, x0[0])
    x1 = np.append(x1, x1[0])
    ax.plot(x0, x1)

    Compare with scipy.optimize.fmin Nelder-Mead¶

    Notice that fmin is much faster here. This is because the function runs very fast, so the internal Xopt bookkeeping overhead dominates.

    5-dimensional Rosenbrock¶

    evaluate_rosenbrock works for arbitrary dimensions, so adding more variables to vocs transforms this problem.

    In [32]:
    Copied! 
    YAML = """
xopt: {}
generator:
  name: neldermead
evaluator:
  function: xopt.resources.test_functions.rosenbrock.evaluate_rosenbrock
vocs:
  variables:
    x1: [-5, 5]
    x2: [-5, 5]
    x3: [-5, 5]
    x4: [-5, 5]
    x5: [-5, 5]
  objectives:
    y: MINIMIZE
"""
X = Xopt(YAML)
    YAML = """ xopt: {} generator: name: neldermead evaluator: function: xopt.resources.test_functions.rosenbrock.evaluate_rosenbrock vocs: variables: x1: [-5, 5] x2: [-5, 5] x3: [-5, 5] x4: [-5, 5] x5: [-5, 5] objectives: y: MINIMIZE """ X = Xopt(YAML)
